{
  "text": "This study revealed the occurrence of An. arabiensis, An. demeilloni, An. christyi, An. funestus s.l, An. pharoensis and An. cinereus in the lowlands and highlands of Southern Ethiopia. Investigation on characterization of breeding habitats showed that stream pools were the main breeding habitats of An. arabiensis. Similarly, the studies in Central and South-Central Ethiopia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] showed the edges and beds of streams serve as breeding habitats for this vector during low rainfall season. On the other hand, An. christyi larvae were found in all kinds of habitats but abundantly in rain pools. Its ability to exist in such type of sites was reported from Central Ethiopia (Akaki) [CITATION_3] .",
